# Web — Telegram Mini App

## Feature-Sliced layout

```
app/       — store, providers, RTK Query base API (parfumApi.ts)
pages/     — route-level composition
widgets/   — larger composites (app-bottom-nav, banner-carousel)
features/  — reusable feature UI (cart, auth, wishlist)
shared/    — API config, utilities, UI primitives
```

Imports flow one-way: `pages` → `widgets` → `features` → `shared`. Do not import upward.

## State

- Server state: RTK Query via `apps/web/src/app/parfumApi.ts`.
- Auth bootstrap: read Telegram `initData` → `POST /auth/telegram` → store JWT → attach `Authorization: Bearer` header.
- No standalone login screen; profile collected at checkout.

## UI

- Components: `@telegram-apps/telegram-ui`.
- SDK: `@telegram-apps/sdk-react` for theme params, back button, viewport.
- Mobile-first; respect safe-area insets.
- Brand tokens as CSS variables synced with Telegram `themeParams`.

## Security

- Never put `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` in `apps/web` — `VITE_*` vars are public in the browser.
